Party Entity Relationship Type Code
A code which identifies the relationship from one entity to another entity.

Valid values are: AGENT-CLIENT = Agent to Client CLIENT-AGENT = Client to Agent PAYPRVDR-CLIENT = Payroll Provider to Client CLIENT-PAYPRVDR = Client to Payroll Provider PTNRSHP-PTNR = Partnership to Partner PTNR-PTNRSHP = Partner to Partnership LTDPTNRSHP-PTNR = Limited Partnership to Partner PTNR-LTDPTNRSHP = Partner to Limited Partnership CMP-DTR = Company to Director DTR-CMP = Director to Company CMP-PBLOFFCR = Company to Public Officer PBLOFFCR-CMP = Public Officer to Company CMP-OFFCBRR = Company to Office Bearer OFFCBRR-CMP = Office Bearer to Company CMP-TRSTEE = Company to Trustee TRSTEE-CMP = Trustee to Company TRST-TRSTEE = Trust to Trustee TRSTEE-TRST = Trustee to Trust SF-TRSTEE = Superannuation Fund to Trustee TRSTEE-SF = Trustee to Superannuation Fund SF-TRSTEEDTR = Superannuation Fund to Trustee Director TRSTEEDTR-SF = Trustee Director to Superannuation Fund SF-MBR = Superannuation Fund to Member MBR-SF = Member to Superannuation Fund ITGRPHD-ITGRPMBR = Income Tax Group Head to Income Tax Group Member ITGRPMBR-ITGRPHD = Income Tax Group Member to Income Tax Group Head NMTDHDCMP-ITGRPMBR = Nominated Head Company to Income Tax Group Member ITGRPMBR-NMTDHDCMP = Income Tax Group Member to Nominated Head Company GSTGRPREP-GRPMBR = GST Group Representative to Group Member GRPMBR-GSTGRPREP = GST Group Member to Group Representative GSTRELGRPPRNPL-MBR = GST Religious Group Principal to Member MBR-GSTRELGRPPRNPL = GST Religious Group Member to Principal
Party Entity Relationship With Agents Code
A code value that represents the existence of relationships between an entity and a requesting agent or other agents.
